theorem closure_interior_closure_interior_eq_closure_interior
    {X : Type*} [TopologicalSpace X] (A : Set X) :
    closure (interior (closure (interior A))) = closure (interior A) := by
  apply subset_antisymm
  · -- `closure (interior (closure (interior A))) ⊆ closure (interior A)`
    have h :
        interior (closure (interior A)) ⊆ closure (interior A) := by
      intro x hx
      -- `interior S ⊆ S` for every set `S`
      exact interior_subset hx
    exact closure_mono h
  · -- `closure (interior A) ⊆ closure (interior (closure (interior A)))`
    have h :
        interior A ⊆ interior (closure (interior A)) :=
      interior_subset_interior_closure_interior (X := X) (A := A)
    exact closure_mono h

theorem closure_interior_eq_of_closed_P2
    {X : Type*} [TopologicalSpace X] {A : Set X}
    (hA : IsClosed A) (hP2 : Topology.P2 A) :
    closure (interior A) = A := by
  -- From `P2` and closedness we obtain `P1`.
  have hP1 : Topology.P1 A :=
    (Topology.P2_closed_imp_P1 (A := A) hA) hP2
  -- A closed set satisfying `P1` is exactly the closure of its interior.
  exact Topology.closed_eq_closure_interior_of_P1 (A := A) hA hP1

theorem closure_interior_union_eq {X : Type*} [TopologicalSpace X] {A B : Set X} :
    closure (interior (A ∪ B)) = closure (interior A) ∪ closure (interior B) := by
  calc
    closure (interior (A ∪ B))
        = closure (interior A ∪ interior B) := by
          simpa [interior_union]
    _ = closure (interior A) ∪ closure (interior B) := by
          simpa [closure_union]

theorem interior_closure_eq_of_clopen {X : Type*} [TopologicalSpace X] {A : Set X}
    (hAopen : IsOpen A) (hAclosed : IsClosed A) :
    interior (closure A) = A := by
  -- Since `A` is closed, its closure equals itself.
  have hClosure : closure A = A := hAclosed.closure_eq
  -- Since `A` is open, its interior equals itself.
  have hInterior : interior A = A := hAopen.interior_eq
  -- Combine the two equalities to reach the goal.
  calc
    interior (closure A) = interior A := by
      simpa [hClosure]
    _ = A := by
      simpa [hInterior]
